<h1>THM Meal 3 – Smoked Ribeye & Garlic Butter Mushrooms (S)</h1>
<div class="time">Estimated Time to Completion: 45–60 minutes</div>

<h2>Equipment</h2>
<ul>
<li>Smoker</li>
<li>Cast iron skillet</li>
<li>Meat thermometer</li>
<li>Tongs</li>
</ul>

<h2>Ingredients</h2>
<ul>
<li>2 ribeye steaks</li>
<li>1 tbsp olive oil</li>
<li>2–3 tbsp butter</li>
</ul>

<h2>Seasoning</h2>
<ul>
<li>1 tsp salt</li>
<li>1 tsp black pepper</li>
<li>1 tsp garlic powder</li>
</ul>

<h2>Sides (S Compliant)</h2>
<ul>
<li>1 lb mushrooms, sliced</li>
<li>2 tbsp butter</li>
<li>2 cloves garlic, minced</li>
<li>Salt</li>
<li>Pepper</li>
<li>Side salad (lettuce, cheese, cucumber, ranch or olive oil)</li>
</ul>

<h2>How To</h2>
<ol>
<li>Preheat smoker: Set to 225°F.</li>
<li>Prep steaks: Pat dry and coat lightly with olive oil.</li>
<li>Season: Apply salt, pepper, and garlic powder.</li>
<li>Smoke: Place steaks on smoker and cook until internal temp reaches 110–115°F.</li>
<li>Sear: Heat cast iron skillet high, add butter, and sear steaks 1–2 minutes per side until desired doneness (130–135°F for medium rare).</li>
<li>Mushrooms: In same skillet, add butter, garlic, and mushrooms. Cook 8–10 minutes until tender.</li>
<li>Rest: Let steaks rest 5–10 minutes.</li>
<li>Salad: Assemble and serve cold.</li>
<li>Serve: Plate steak with mushrooms and salad.</li>
</ol>

